ation: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":31,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When William de Mauduit was born in 1228, in Wiltshire, England, his father, Thomas De Mauduit, was 45 and his mother, Mrs Thomas De Manduit, was 43. He had at least 2 sons with Eugenia FitzWarin. He died on 4 April 1264, at the age of 36."},"et":{"1228–4 April 1264":"1228–4. aprill 1264","1228–1264":"1228–1264","1228–1307":"1228–1307","1248–1271":"1248–1271","1254–1300":"1254–1300","1183–1244":"1183–1244","1185–Female":"1185–Surnud","1264":"1264","before 28 July 1244":"enne 28. juulit 1244","1185":"1185","1183":"1183","1271":"1271","1228":"1228","1248":"1248","1259":"1259","1300":"1300","1244":"1244","1254":"1254","4 April 1264":"4. aprill 1264","1307":"1307","Warminister, Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England","Warminister,,Wiltshire,England":"Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1228–4 April 1264":"1228–4. huhtikuuta 1264","1228–1264":"1228–1264","1228–1307":"1228–1307","1248–1271":"1248–1271","1254–1300":"1254–1300","1183–1244":"1183–1244","1185–Female":"1185–Kuollut","1264":"1264","before 28 July 1244":"ennen vuotta 28. heinäkuuta 1244","1185":"1185","1183":"1183","1271":"1271","1228":"1228","1248":"1248","1259":"1259","1300":"1300","1244":"1244","1254":"1254","4 April 1264":"4. huhtikuuta 1264","1307":"1307","Warminister, Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, E